%% Data Flow Diagram - ODH Notebook Controller (kubeflow)
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User Browser
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Proxy as kube-rbac-proxy sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (service-ca cert)
    participant Notebook as Notebook Application<br/>8888/TCP HTTP (loopback)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as ODH Notebook Controller
    participant Webhook as Notebook Webhook<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over User,Notebook: Flow 1: Notebook Access via Gateway API (Auth Mode)
    User->>Gateway: GET /notebook/{ns}/{name}<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Gateway->>Proxy: Forward via HTTPRoute<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (service serving cert)
    Proxy->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(verb: get, resource: notebooks)
    K8sAPI-->>Proxy: Allowed/Denied
    Proxy->>Notebook: Proxy to 127.0.0.1:8888<br/>HTTP (plaintext loopback)<br/>X-Auth-Request-User/Groups headers
    Notebook-->>Proxy: Response
    Proxy-->>Gateway: HTTPS Response
    Gateway-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over K8sAPI,Webhook: Flow 2: Notebook Creation Webhook Mutation
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl create Notebook CR
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-notebook-v1<br/>HTTPS/443, mTLS (API server client cert)
    Webhook->>K8sAPI: Read ImageStreams, ConfigMaps, Secrets<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: AdmissionResponse with patches<br/>(inject sidecar, resolve images, mount certs)

    Note over Controller,K8sAPI: Flow 3: Controller Reconciliation
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch Notebook CRs<br/>HTTPS/443, ServiceAccount token
    K8sAPI-->>Controller: Notebook event
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute (central NS)<br/>HTTPS/443
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ReferenceGrant (user NS)<br/>HTTPS/443
    Controller->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy, Service,<br/>ConfigMap, SA, CRB<br/>HTTPS/443
